WEBVTT

00:03.235 --> 00:06.968
300 miles above the Earth,

00:07.040 --> 00:09.669
Dr. Jonas Venture Jr.
is hard at work

00:09.743 --> 00:11.302
on his Gargantua-2
space station.

00:11.378 --> 00:14.143
His life hangs
by a thin oxygen tube...

00:14.214 --> 00:15.204
[air hisses ]

00:15.281 --> 00:17.876
...manufactured by a recently
acquired subsidiary

00:17.951 --> 00:19.351
of Impossible Industries.

00:19.419 --> 00:20.887
Meanwhile, closer to home,

00:20.954 --> 00:23.549
Girl Hitler addresses
the General Assembly

00:23.623 --> 00:26.491
of the United Nations,
but she is instantly killed

00:26.559 --> 00:29.222
when her microphone
suffers a short.

00:29.295 --> 00:32.390
Elsewhere, the Monarch visits
his local ATM,

00:32.465 --> 00:34.366
only to discover
his trust fund is empty.

00:34.434 --> 00:37.962
His bank, also recently acquired
by Impossible Industries,

00:38.038 --> 00:41.634
has just been robbed --
and they're not FDIC.

00:41.708 --> 00:45.509
Tempestuous as he is foolish,
he blames his wife,

00:45.578 --> 00:47.604
but she's already dead,

00:47.680 --> 00:50.149
murdered by a pair of
well-placed sleeper agents

00:50.216 --> 00:52.310
within the Monarch's
own ranks

00:52.385 --> 00:54.047
but made to look
like the work

00:54.120 --> 00:56.589
of a lowly, lovelorn henchman

00:56.656 --> 01:00.024
who has, of late, exhibited
signs of instability.

01:00.093 --> 01:03.393
And all the while,
the Guild of Calamitous Intent

01:03.463 --> 01:07.093
loses member after member
to sudden mysterious deaths,

01:07.167 --> 01:11.104
and the weight of failure
is simply too heavy

01:11.171 --> 01:13.367
for the Sovereign's
thin white shoulders to bear.

01:13.440 --> 01:16.808
What do these hapless fools
all have in common?

01:16.876 --> 01:19.277
They dared to betray the members
of the Revenge Society!

01:23.183 --> 01:25.743
So, what do you think?
Hmm.

01:25.819 --> 01:28.015
Frankly, it's a little...
killy.

01:28.088 --> 01:29.249
I like it.
I'm in.

01:29.322 --> 01:31.518
Hey, and are we married
to that name --

01:31.591 --> 01:32.581
"Revenge Society"?

01:32.659 --> 01:35.128
I was thinking perhaps
"The Violet Hour."

01:35.195 --> 01:36.527
That's T.S. Eliot.

01:36.596 --> 01:37.620
Oh, that's awful.

01:37.697 --> 01:39.689
It sounds like we should be
headlining the Lilith Festival.

01:39.766 --> 01:42.031
I was thinking
maybe "The Purple Pros"

01:42.102 --> 01:44.367
because we all wear
the purple und --

01:44.437 --> 01:45.530
The name stays.

01:45.605 --> 01:47.972
And you don't get a vote,
Werner --

01:48.041 --> 01:49.407
not till you've first proved
your loyalty.

01:49.476 --> 01:50.375
Just a formality.

01:50.443 --> 01:51.843
Ja, I understand.

01:51.911 --> 01:54.244
We have a similar ritual in
the Elite Underlandian Guard.

01:54.314 --> 01:55.805
[ bones cracking ]

01:55.882 --> 01:57.077
- Oh, dear God.
- Mother of pearl!

01:57.150 --> 01:58.448
What?

01:58.518 --> 01:59.986
Oh, we -- we just
wanted you to sign...

02:00.053 --> 02:00.884
[ knocking on door]

02:00.954 --> 02:02.752
...a piece of, uh...

02:02.822 --> 02:04.916
Uh, just a minute!

02:04.991 --> 02:06.482
Violet Hour, hide!

02:06.559 --> 02:07.857
And take him with you!

02:14.634 --> 02:15.624
[ keypad beeps ]

02:15.702 --> 02:18.695
Three pipin'-hot coffees --
just the way you like 'em.

02:18.771 --> 02:20.763
[ up-tempo music plays ]

02:23.309 --> 02:24.709
Excelsior, faithful readers!

02:24.777 --> 02:27.337
It's your roving reporter,
Deanie V.,

02:27.413 --> 02:28.745
bringing you
the latest edition

02:28.815 --> 02:30.113
of the "Venture Home News,"

02:30.183 --> 02:31.981
all the way
from New York City,

02:32.051 --> 02:34.316
home of the world-famous
Impossible Industries,

02:34.387 --> 02:36.686
where yours truly has just
landed a summer internship.

02:36.756 --> 02:39.920
I thought maybe Pop pulled some
strings to get me accepted,

02:39.993 --> 02:41.393
but the nice-smelling lady
who hired me

02:41.461 --> 02:43.327
said she'd never
heard of him.

02:43.396 --> 02:46.594
And, boy, Professor Impossible
sure was surprised to see me.

02:46.666 --> 02:49.727
Yeah, I never got the feeling
he liked me very much before,

02:49.802 --> 02:51.566
but on my very first day
on the job,

02:51.638 --> 02:53.903
he promoted me
to his executive assistant.

02:53.973 --> 02:55.839
Guess they're a little
short-staffed at the moment.

02:55.909 --> 02:57.468
Uh, maybe the recession?

02:57.544 --> 02:59.740
So far, I haven't gotten to do
any science stuff,

02:59.812 --> 03:00.802
uh, but that's okay.

03:00.880 --> 03:02.212
Mostly I answer phones,
sort mail,

03:02.282 --> 03:05.081
and make sure he gets
his morning coffee,

03:05.151 --> 03:06.619
just the way he likes it --

03:06.686 --> 03:08.120
with milk and sugar --

03:08.188 --> 03:11.488
and also one black and also
one black with two sugars.

03:11.558 --> 03:12.992
It's no wonder he's so jumpy.

03:13.059 --> 03:14.459
Then again,
he might just be nervous

03:14.527 --> 03:17.019
about the big new project
he's launching.

03:17.096 --> 03:18.621
It's so
super-hush-hush secret, though,

03:18.698 --> 03:20.860
even I don't know
what it is yet.

03:20.934 --> 03:23.836
So, let me tell you
about my new home.

03:23.903 --> 03:26.395
Making it in New York on
an unpaid intern's un-salary

03:26.472 --> 03:27.872
is pretty tough,

03:27.941 --> 03:29.409
but Hank found me
a rent-controlled apartment

03:29.475 --> 03:30.306
in the want ads.

03:30.376 --> 03:32.106
The ad said it was cozy,

03:32.178 --> 03:35.273
and the landlord said
a guy died in here,

03:35.348 --> 03:37.317
but with a little thrifty
redecorating,

03:37.383 --> 03:38.874
I've managed
to make it a home.

03:38.952 --> 03:41.820
I don't have much money
for entertainment,

03:41.888 --> 03:43.720
so most nights I just stay home
and make my own fun.

03:43.790 --> 03:46.259
I also learned to cook
for myself,

03:46.326 --> 03:47.919
and the K rations
Sergeant Hatred left me

03:47.994 --> 03:49.360
should last me
all summer long.

03:49.429 --> 03:52.228
Well, that's about
all the time I have

03:52.298 --> 03:53.766
for this edition
of the "Venture Home News."

03:53.833 --> 03:55.267
This is Deanie V.,

03:55.335 --> 03:56.769
saying see you next time,
Venture-oos!

04:00.139 --> 04:02.904
[ knocking on door]

04:02.976 --> 04:04.706
Who is it?

04:04.777 --> 04:06.040
Open up, boy.

04:06.112 --> 04:09.207
I think the rats can smell
the combos in my bag.

04:09.282 --> 04:10.443
Hello, son!
- Daddy!

04:10.516 --> 04:11.814
Surprised to see me?

04:11.884 --> 04:13.182
Oh, geez, look at this place.

04:13.253 --> 04:15.279
What, are you waiting for
Jacob Riis to take your picture?

04:15.355 --> 04:16.288
What are you doing here?

04:16.356 --> 04:19.622
I got hooked!
I'm bonkers for Broadway!

04:19.692 --> 04:22.491
Yeah, after Hatred and I took in
"The Music Man" last week,

04:22.562 --> 04:24.554
I bought my walkman back
from Hank's store

04:24.631 --> 04:25.860
and loaded it up
with show tunes.

04:25.932 --> 04:27.730
Now I can't get enough of that
sweet stuff.

04:27.800 --> 04:28.631
Hank has a store?

04:28.701 --> 04:30.636
Ooh! I want to take in
all the big shows.

04:30.703 --> 04:32.228
Oh, do you mind if I crash here
for about a week?

04:32.305 --> 04:33.136
A week?!

04:33.206 --> 04:34.504
I don't know
if there's room here --

04:34.574 --> 04:35.473
I get it.

04:35.541 --> 04:37.669
You're worried the old man's
gonna cramp your style.

04:37.744 --> 04:40.236
Here, look -- whenever you want
the place to yourself,

04:40.313 --> 04:41.941
just tie this
around the doorknob,

04:42.015 --> 04:45.850
and presto -- no moleste --
old college trick.

04:45.918 --> 04:48.114
In fact, I think
this <i>is</i> my tie from college.

04:48.187 --> 04:50.656
My <i>lucky</i> tie -- meow.

04:50.723 --> 04:52.783
Yeah, only it goes
on the <i>outside.</i>

04:52.859 --> 04:56.660
Well [yawns] I sure would love
to catch up with you, Pop,

04:56.729 --> 04:58.254
but I have work
in the morning, so I --

04:58.331 --> 05:00.129
Well, go on.
Go on.

05:00.199 --> 05:01.565
Don't let me get
in your way.

05:01.634 --> 05:03.159
Just go about your business.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.933
You'll never even know
I was here.

05:06.005 --> 05:07.769
♪ Ya ♪
♪ Dat dat dat dat ♪

05:07.840 --> 05:09.866
♪ Dat dat da ♪
♪ Yada dada da, yada dada da ♪

05:09.942 --> 05:10.841
Oh, don't mind me.

05:10.910 --> 05:13.072
I had this dynamite idea
for a new musical.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.342
Just wanted to jot down
a few notes

05:15.415 --> 05:16.405
before I forget them.

05:16.482 --> 05:18.417
Okay...
[ keys clacking ]

05:18.484 --> 05:19.645
♪ Ba ba ♪

05:19.719 --> 05:21.210
♪ Yada dada dada ♪

05:21.287 --> 05:24.155
♪ Yada ♪
♪ Yada, yada, yada ♪

05:24.223 --> 05:25.316
♪ Dat dat dat da ♪

05:25.391 --> 05:26.689
Ahh.

05:26.759 --> 05:27.749
Ohh. Ugh!

05:27.827 --> 05:31.161
Say, Baron Underbheit,
what's all the hubbub?

05:31.230 --> 05:33.961
Ohh! I just want
to arch my nemesis,

05:34.033 --> 05:36.195
but I can't understand
all these forms!

05:36.269 --> 05:39.000
Und I can't get anyone
from The Guild on the phone.

05:39.072 --> 05:42.975
Sounds like you two need
The Revenge Society.

05:43.042 --> 05:44.567
Now, uh, gentlemen,

05:44.644 --> 05:47.637
before we start interviewing
potential candidates,

05:47.714 --> 05:49.876
You need to keep one thing
in mind --"S.P.A.W.M."

05:49.949 --> 05:51.542
That awful comic book?

05:51.617 --> 05:52.607
Oh, and that movie?

05:52.685 --> 05:54.051
What was Martin Sheen
thinking?

05:54.120 --> 05:55.315
Not "Spawn."

05:55.388 --> 05:56.822
S.P.A.W.M. --
it's an acronym

05:56.889 --> 05:58.790
for the classic panoply
of powers

05:58.858 --> 06:00.349
every professional
villain team needs --

06:00.426 --> 06:03.988
speed, power, air,
water, magic.

06:04.063 --> 06:06.396
The "w" can also stand for
"wind" or "weather,"

06:06.466 --> 06:08.901
but you definitely need at least
one elemental in the mix.

06:08.968 --> 06:11.597
Ooh, like a fire guy --
that would be cool.

06:11.671 --> 06:14.732
Well, guess what, chicken butt,
fellas -- good news.

06:14.807 --> 06:17.106
Aah!

06:17.176 --> 06:19.077
Eh? What'd I tell you?

06:19.145 --> 06:21.376
Yes, sir.
Thanks to this little dynamo,

06:21.447 --> 06:22.745
Impossible Industries
is 100% green!

06:25.485 --> 06:28.182
And you didn't think you had it
in you to be a supervillain.

06:28.254 --> 06:31.588
This is the most deliciously
evil thing I've ever seen.

06:31.657 --> 06:35.094
DEAN:
Uh, Professor Impossible?
I'm taking my lunch now.

06:35.161 --> 06:36.424
[ horns honking ]

06:36.496 --> 06:38.931
Psst! Psst!

06:38.998 --> 06:40.933
[ clears throat ]
Dean?

06:41.000 --> 06:43.265
Dean, over here!
Sit down and act natural.

06:43.336 --> 06:45.771
I thought you were
taking me to lunch.

06:45.838 --> 06:47.204
Better yet --
I brought lunch to you.

06:47.273 --> 06:48.263
Sack lunch -- here you go.

06:48.341 --> 06:49.775
We're sharing the fries.

06:49.842 --> 06:52.641
Anyway, I have an ulterior
motive for asking you here.

06:52.712 --> 06:54.044
I need you
to perform a little,

06:54.113 --> 06:57.379
uh, shall we say,
industrial espionage.

06:57.450 --> 06:59.544
[sighs ]
Pop, even if I knew

06:59.619 --> 07:01.110
what Professor Impossible's big
secret project was,

07:01.187 --> 07:03.486
I'm not allowed to --
- Not that. Wait.

07:03.556 --> 07:04.854
He's working
on a secret project?

07:04.924 --> 07:06.392
What is it?
Oh, whatever. Never mind.

07:06.459 --> 07:07.620
Just take this.

07:07.693 --> 07:08.592
[ coughs ]

07:08.661 --> 07:10.357
I'm gonna need
two dozen copies,

07:10.430 --> 07:11.363
stapled and collated.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.798
And be sure each one
gets one of these.

07:13.866 --> 07:14.799
What is this?

07:14.867 --> 07:16.495
My musical!
I finished it!

07:16.569 --> 07:19.038
It's all about my childhood,
my adventures...

07:19.105 --> 07:21.233
♪ My secret longing
for a better world ♪

07:21.307 --> 07:22.240
[laughs ]

07:22.308 --> 07:25.301
I'm gonna hit every agent
and producer in town.

07:25.378 --> 07:26.710
Dred Scott!
What is he doing here?

07:26.779 --> 07:29.180
Well, <i>you</i> were the one
eavesdropping.

07:29.248 --> 07:31.740
He mumbled something about
industrial espionage,

07:31.818 --> 07:33.980
and then he just kept talking
about "Annie Get Your Gun."

07:34.053 --> 07:35.521
Do you think
it's some type of code?

07:35.588 --> 07:36.954
[gasps ]
He's on to us.

07:37.023 --> 07:38.491
You're both
being paranoid.

07:38.558 --> 07:40.083
Don't you see what this is?

07:40.159 --> 07:42.822
This is opportunity
knocking at our door.

07:42.895 --> 07:44.261
Who disfigured you for life

07:44.330 --> 07:46.856
and helped Girl Hitler
steal your throne?

07:46.933 --> 07:48.265
Who seduced your wife,

07:48.334 --> 07:51.202
then passed her off to his
brother for sloppy seconds?

07:51.270 --> 07:52.704
I'll tell you who --

07:52.772 --> 07:56.004
the very same cretin who allied
with his own enemies

07:56.075 --> 07:57.600
to thwart me
at Cremation Creek

07:57.677 --> 07:58.940
and the Battle for the Orb.

07:59.011 --> 08:01.003
Gentlemen,
The Revenge Society just landed

08:01.080 --> 08:03.606
its first assignment --

08:03.683 --> 08:06.448
kill Dr. Venture!

08:06.519 --> 08:09.114
What? Like, right now?

08:09.188 --> 08:11.180
Mmm. Oh.
[watch beeps ]

08:11.257 --> 08:13.055
Oh! Curtain's in 10 minutes.
Better hail a cab.

08:13.125 --> 08:14.525
Taxi!

08:14.594 --> 08:16.426
Now, I still have to write
all the music,

08:16.496 --> 08:18.465
but the real trick will be
finding a good Rusty.

08:18.531 --> 08:20.363
I need someone with a voice,

08:20.433 --> 08:22.561
real stage presence,
sex appeal.

08:22.635 --> 08:24.536
Oh, and I'm probably gonna
have to stay in town

08:24.604 --> 08:25.697
for an extra week or two.

08:25.771 --> 08:27.467
Oh, I don't know, pop.

08:27.540 --> 08:29.873
Oh, no, I wouldn't dream
of asking you, son.

08:29.942 --> 08:32.844
I mean, you look the part,
but you're a terrible actor.

08:32.912 --> 08:34.278
No. What?
I-I mean --

08:34.347 --> 08:35.610
Just awful.

08:35.681 --> 08:37.445
Look, we can talk about it
at home tonight, okay?

08:37.517 --> 08:40.282
Have fun at work, son.
Oh, make those copies.

08:40.352 --> 08:44.017
Broadway district,
and step on it.

08:44.090 --> 08:46.491
Hey!
Coming up next on Taxi TV,

08:46.559 --> 08:48.084
we've got great places
around the city to eat,

08:48.160 --> 08:50.595
and we'll be talking
to a local man...

08:50.663 --> 08:53.189
Ugh.
Touch screens never work.

08:53.266 --> 08:56.634
Greetings, Dr. Venture.

08:56.702 --> 08:59.399
This is The Revenge Society.

08:59.472 --> 09:00.667
[laughs evilly]

09:00.740 --> 09:03.733
Now that I have
your undivided attention,

09:03.809 --> 09:05.072
listen to me very carefully.

09:05.144 --> 09:07.670
We have -- hello?
Are you listening to me?

09:07.747 --> 09:10.581
♪ Yada-chanted evening ♪

09:10.650 --> 09:11.845
♪ Stranger ♪

09:11.918 --> 09:13.511
Um...
uh, wh--

09:13.586 --> 09:16.681
Now we're cooking with gas.

09:16.756 --> 09:17.655
[gas hissing ]

09:17.723 --> 09:19.954
Nighty-night,
Dr. Venture.

09:20.026 --> 09:22.552
Pleasant screams.

09:23.596 --> 09:25.155
[ coughs ]

09:25.998 --> 09:27.660
[tires screeching ]

09:27.733 --> 09:28.723
[ horns honking ]

09:31.304 --> 09:33.705
Gah!

09:33.773 --> 09:34.706
Whoa!

09:34.774 --> 09:36.766
[grunting ]

09:42.682 --> 09:43.513
[ horns honking ]

09:47.119 --> 09:48.280
End of the line, sir.

09:48.354 --> 09:50.346
Please remember to take
all your personal belongings

09:50.423 --> 09:52.449
and be sure to tip your driver.
[ chuckles ]

09:52.525 --> 09:53.754
What?
This is funny to you?

09:53.826 --> 09:54.794
I just almost got killed.

09:54.860 --> 09:56.021
Get the hell out of my way.

09:56.095 --> 09:58.030
I'm gonna miss the overture.

09:58.097 --> 09:59.087
Fucking tourists.

09:59.165 --> 10:01.031
Okay, that was crap.

10:01.100 --> 10:02.432
What the hell happened there?

10:02.501 --> 10:04.527
I can't believe he ditched
the cab fare.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.004
Zounds!
That Venture is wily prey!

10:06.072 --> 10:08.132
Why on earth did you
put the sleep gas

10:08.207 --> 10:09.175
in the front of the cab?

10:09.241 --> 10:10.937
I thought you were supposed
to be a genius!

10:11.010 --> 10:12.945
Well, I've never done
this kind of thing before.

10:13.012 --> 10:14.378
It's our first mission
as a team.

10:14.447 --> 10:16.245
There are bound to be
a few hiccups.

10:16.315 --> 10:18.250
Let's not squabble, Hamilton.

10:18.317 --> 10:20.343
Very well.
Positives?

10:20.419 --> 10:23.321
On the up side, Werner did
an excellent job as the cabbie -

10:23.389 --> 10:25.085
until you gassed him!

10:25.157 --> 10:26.955
All right, that's just
passive-aggressive, friend.

10:27.026 --> 10:28.619
I see exactly
what you're doing there.

10:28.694 --> 10:31.163
Sorry I'm late,
Professor Impossible.

10:31.230 --> 10:32.994
You see, my dad stopped by
for lunch and the --

10:33.065 --> 10:34.931
[gasps ]
Phantom Limb!

10:35.001 --> 10:37.095
What the hell was
that shit out there?

10:37.169 --> 10:38.762
Baron Underbeit!

10:38.838 --> 10:41.000
Now, now, Dean,
this isn't what it appears,

10:41.073 --> 10:47.172
so let's all try
to just keep calm.

10:47.246 --> 10:48.475
[whistle blows ]

10:48.547 --> 10:50.106
[groans ]

10:50.182 --> 10:51.309
Aah!

10:51.384 --> 10:52.477
[electricity crackles ]

10:52.551 --> 10:54.144
Hot sandwich!

10:54.220 --> 10:57.156
You've murdered
the Venture boy.

11:00.493 --> 11:03.463
[ breathing rapidly]

11:03.529 --> 11:04.963
Huh?
Aah!

11:05.031 --> 11:07.125
Ah, good.
You're up.

11:07.199 --> 11:09.168
Oh, thank goodness.
You got away from them?

11:09.235 --> 11:10.794
[ chuckling ]
Oh, no, Dean.

11:10.870 --> 11:12.839
Those fellows are with <i>me.</i>
- Aah!

11:12.905 --> 11:15.898
I think maybe it's time
I let someone in

11:15.975 --> 11:17.876
on my big secret project.

11:17.943 --> 11:19.172
Our secret project.

11:19.245 --> 11:20.907
You see,
I've known Werner there

11:20.980 --> 11:22.380
since he was
a student of mine.

11:22.448 --> 11:25.008
And Hamilton and I go
all the way back

11:25.084 --> 11:27.019
to your grandfather's
Boys' Brigade days.

11:27.086 --> 11:29.817
But their lives
took a different turn

11:29.889 --> 11:31.653
when they both suffered
horrible, disfiguring accidents

11:31.724 --> 11:33.955
which left them
unable to work.

11:34.026 --> 11:37.428
They soon found themselves
on the wrong side of the law

11:37.496 --> 11:39.124
just to make ends meet.

11:39.198 --> 11:41.565
And now that they've served
their time,

11:41.634 --> 11:43.262
they're looking for a way to
become useful,

11:43.335 --> 11:45.634
productive members
of society again --

11:45.705 --> 11:47.367
only no one will hire them

11:47.440 --> 11:48.874
because of their
criminal records.

11:48.941 --> 11:51.536
Now, does that sound like
the America

11:51.610 --> 11:53.602
you want to live in,
young Dean?

11:53.679 --> 11:55.978
- No, sir.
- Me neither, youngster.

11:56.048 --> 11:58.381
So, that's why,
starting tomorrow,

11:58.451 --> 12:00.420
Impossible Industries
is launching

12:00.486 --> 12:03.888
the Impossi-Care Second Chance
Employment Program.

12:03.956 --> 12:05.652
That's what all
the secrecy was about?

12:05.725 --> 12:07.125
[laughs ]
Of course.

12:07.193 --> 12:10.630
What? You didn't think I went
all evil or something, did you?

12:10.696 --> 12:12.255
[laughs ]
Oh, that is rich.

12:12.331 --> 12:15.233
How long have you been working
for me now, anyway?

12:15.301 --> 12:16.166
About a week.

12:16.235 --> 12:19.467
Well, I think you're way overdue
for a promotion.

12:19.538 --> 12:21.234
- I-I am?
- Yes, sirree.

12:21.307 --> 12:23.208
Starting tomorrow,
I'm making you

12:23.275 --> 12:26.074
our new head of human
resources!

12:26.145 --> 12:27.909
- Really?
- Good night, lad!

12:27.980 --> 12:29.846
Remember -- promotion,
human resources, me not evil!

12:29.915 --> 12:31.611
Good night!

12:31.684 --> 12:34.017
Wow.
[sighs ]

12:34.086 --> 12:35.418
Ow!
- Sorry.

12:35.488 --> 12:38.287
Th-There was a prowler
on the fire escape earlier.

12:38.357 --> 12:39.757
Did you make my copies?

12:39.825 --> 12:41.088
[ indistinct shouting ]

12:41.160 --> 12:44.062
Okay, people, I want
two orderly lines!

12:44.130 --> 12:47.157
If your name starts
with "A" through "J,"

12:47.233 --> 12:49.202
I want you to line up
over here to my left.

12:49.268 --> 12:51.601
K's through R's,
you're on the right.

12:51.670 --> 12:53.969
What if your name starts
with no earthly letter?

12:54.039 --> 12:57.373
Ugh, I thought Manhattan was
the epicenter of supervillainy.

12:57.443 --> 12:59.742
It looks more like the island
of misfit toys out there.

12:59.812 --> 13:01.906
Come on.
Give me some room here.

13:01.981 --> 13:03.779
Well, it wasn't designed
for three.

13:03.849 --> 13:04.908
Who knew?

13:04.984 --> 13:07.283
Okay, Dean, who's first?

13:07.353 --> 13:09.447
Polygamy! Mr. Polygamy!

13:09.522 --> 13:11.514
And this is Mrs. Polygamy,
Mrs. Polygamy,

13:11.590 --> 13:13.320
Mrs. Polygamy,
and Mrs. Polygamy.

13:13.392 --> 13:18.160
So, what exactly does
magic underwear do?

13:18.230 --> 13:19.323
Chuk-luk!

13:19.398 --> 13:20.491
Zhhhhh.

13:20.566 --> 13:23.161
Um, was something
supposed to happen?

13:23.235 --> 13:26.262
You didn't see that?
I just grew bigger.

13:26.338 --> 13:27.101
No, you didn't.

13:27.173 --> 13:30.507
I did -- like, at least
2 inches, maybe 3.

13:30.576 --> 13:31.509
He saw it.

13:31.577 --> 13:33.068
I think, um...

13:33.145 --> 13:34.738
yes, I think he might have.

13:34.814 --> 13:37.784
No. Look! Look --
he's on his toes!

13:37.850 --> 13:38.840
Fat Chance.

13:38.918 --> 13:41.513
And before you make your
little weight-ist judgments,

13:41.587 --> 13:44.352
I got this way 'cause of a
botched scientific experiment.

13:44.423 --> 13:45.584
You are preaching
to the choir, friend.

13:45.658 --> 13:46.523
Tell me about it.

13:46.592 --> 13:49.187
Yeah, so, basically the accident
transformed my body

13:49.261 --> 13:51.662
into a portal
to another dimension,

13:51.730 --> 13:53.221
and now I can pull stuff out
of time and space

13:53.299 --> 13:55.029
through my duodenum.
Boom.

13:55.100 --> 13:57.126
And you find that...
useful?

13:57.203 --> 13:58.796
Sometimes.

13:58.871 --> 13:59.861
Ladyhawk Johnson,

13:59.939 --> 14:02.033
and the little fella buzzing
in your ear there

14:02.107 --> 14:04.906
is my husband and partner
of 40 years, Mr. Lyndon Bee.

14:04.977 --> 14:07.970
And what are
<i>your</i> special powers?

14:08.047 --> 14:10.448
Well, by night,
I turn into a hawk,

14:10.516 --> 14:12.075
but by day, he's a bee,

14:12.151 --> 14:13.676
and never the twain shall meet,

14:13.752 --> 14:15.653
except during a eclipse,
of course!

14:15.721 --> 14:18.816
Well, of course, we'll have
to interview Mr. Bee separately,

14:18.891 --> 14:20.757
when he's, um...

14:20.826 --> 14:22.727
Not a bee.

14:22.795 --> 14:24.787
Well, tell him "hi" for me,
will you?

14:24.864 --> 14:31.293
So, um, I-I-I can't seem
to find your résumé.

14:31.370 --> 14:34.704
Uh, Dean, can you bring me
the paperwork on, uh --

14:34.773 --> 14:37.072
What was your name again?

14:37.142 --> 14:39.304
So, um, how did
you hear about

14:39.378 --> 14:40.573
The Revenge Society?

14:40.646 --> 14:42.410
[ breathing heavily]

14:42.481 --> 14:44.643
Uh...where might we know
some of your work from?

14:46.318 --> 14:47.513
[ breathing heavily]

14:47.586 --> 14:50.021
Aah!
He's not on the list.

14:50.089 --> 14:52.024
I-I'm sorry.
I don't know how he got in here.

14:52.091 --> 14:54.617
And he's got a knife...

14:54.693 --> 14:55.922
super power.

14:55.995 --> 14:57.657
Brick frog!

14:57.730 --> 14:59.028
Thank you!

14:59.098 --> 15:01.431
Ugh. Worse than useless.

15:01.500 --> 15:04.527
Hardly any of them are worthy
of The Revenge Society.

15:04.603 --> 15:06.595
Dean, that'll be all
for today.

15:06.672 --> 15:08.937
Uh, you still have
one more interview, sir.

15:09.008 --> 15:11.204
This gentleman's been waiting
since sundown.

15:11.277 --> 15:13.212
[siren wailing ]

15:13.279 --> 15:14.474
Phew.

15:14.546 --> 15:16.378
[shouting indistinctly]

15:16.448 --> 15:18.110
What?

15:18.183 --> 15:19.549
[groans ]

15:19.618 --> 15:21.450
Ew.

15:21.520 --> 15:22.510
Yes!

15:22.588 --> 15:24.454
Quick -- what's the most popular
musical in Germany?

15:24.523 --> 15:26.116
What? Uh --

15:26.191 --> 15:27.819
"Starlight Express,"
exactly!

15:27.893 --> 15:29.122
Whoo!

15:29.194 --> 15:31.823
Yeah, roller skates --
the whole cast.

15:31.897 --> 15:34.059
"Rust!" needs a gimmick to hook
the foreign investors.

15:34.133 --> 15:35.624
- But why did you --
- Oh, that?

15:35.701 --> 15:37.897
Yeah, it kept getting
caught in my wheel,

15:37.970 --> 15:39.598
so I just tossed it out there
with the rest of the --

15:39.672 --> 15:41.402
Oh! You --
You thought I was --

15:41.473 --> 15:43.499
He knows his old man.

15:43.575 --> 15:44.634
Why is this here?!

15:44.710 --> 15:46.303
It was blocking
my center stage.

15:46.378 --> 15:48.404
I have to go to the toilet!

15:48.480 --> 15:50.415
Number one?
Use the tub. That's what I do.

15:50.482 --> 15:52.314
Urrrrgh!

15:52.384 --> 15:55.821
Oh, mein gott, you guys
will never guess

15:55.888 --> 15:58.483
what I found
on the copy machine.

15:58.557 --> 16:00.082
[laughs ]

16:00.159 --> 16:02.754
♪ Yada da Rusty ♪

16:02.828 --> 16:05.059
♪ Super ♪

16:05.130 --> 16:08.225
♪ My name is Rusty ♪

16:08.300 --> 16:10.895
♪ It's Rusty Venture ♪

16:10.970 --> 16:12.632
♪ Boy adventurer ♪

16:12.705 --> 16:15.368
Oh, that's good.
That's good.

16:15.441 --> 16:18.001
[sighs ]

16:18.077 --> 16:19.272
That guy bothering you?

16:19.345 --> 16:20.506
Kind of.

16:20.579 --> 16:21.512
Shh. I understand.

16:21.580 --> 16:23.344
You can't talk.
You need help.

16:23.415 --> 16:25.281
Just blink twice
if he's your pimp.

16:25.351 --> 16:27.286
No. What?
No, he's my dad.

16:27.353 --> 16:28.184
Oh.

16:28.253 --> 16:30.745
So, uh, what brings you two
to the big apple, then?

16:30.823 --> 16:34.123
Well, I got this internship
at Impossible Industries, but --

16:34.193 --> 16:35.354
Superscience, huh?

16:35.427 --> 16:36.895
Yeah, I used to be
in that racket myself.

16:36.962 --> 16:38.328
Really?
Why'd you give it up?

16:38.397 --> 16:39.729
Pfft.
You're lookin' at it.

16:39.798 --> 16:42.495
Yeah, I had a little
mishap in the lab

16:42.568 --> 16:44.935
back when I was working on
my irradiated spider thesis -

16:45.004 --> 16:47.030
kind of soured me on the whole
superscience deal.

16:47.106 --> 16:48.005
Mm.

16:48.073 --> 16:51.043
Yeah, I'm not really sure I want
to be a superscientist, either,

16:51.110 --> 16:53.705
but my dad really wants me to
follow in his footsteps.

16:53.779 --> 16:56.476
Yeah, I can see why you really
wouldn't want to do that.

16:56.548 --> 16:58.483
But, hey, you're working with
Professor Impossible now.

16:58.550 --> 16:59.540
That's "A"-list.

16:59.618 --> 17:01.484
You could practically
write your own ticket.

17:01.553 --> 17:02.646
Yeah, you'd think, right?

17:02.721 --> 17:04.713
I mean, I thought things would
be different there,

17:04.790 --> 17:06.691
but it's just
the same old story --

17:06.759 --> 17:07.988
do nothing all day.

17:08.060 --> 17:10.051
Then a bunch of guys in costumes
come out and bother you.

17:10.128 --> 17:11.825
I could get that at home.

17:11.896 --> 17:15.527
Sounds like somebody would
rather be doing something else.

17:15.601 --> 17:18.502
What I really want to be
is a boy reporter.

17:18.569 --> 17:22.905
I'm -- I'm sorry.
What is that enchanting music?

17:22.974 --> 17:25.672
♪ The dreams I buried ♪

17:25.743 --> 17:28.236
♪ with robot fingers ♪

17:28.313 --> 17:30.839
Daddy?
Daddy, I need to talk to you.

17:30.916 --> 17:31.781
♪ Why, Rusty ♪

17:31.850 --> 17:34.319
I've given it a lot of thought,
and I've come to a decision.

17:34.386 --> 17:36.082
Are you listening?

17:36.155 --> 17:37.418
♪ The man of action ♪

17:37.489 --> 17:39.549
♪ like muscle mothers ♪

17:39.625 --> 17:40.593
Fine.

17:40.659 --> 17:42.992
♪ not brothers ♪

17:43.062 --> 17:45.588
♪ on grand adventures ♪

17:45.664 --> 17:48.099
♪ They pushed me with them ♪

17:48.167 --> 17:50.227
♪ for mayhem ♪

17:50.302 --> 17:53.238
♪ Who's Rusty? ♪

17:54.440 --> 17:56.375
♪ I'm Rusty-y-y ♪

17:56.442 --> 18:02.313
♪ I'm Rusty-y-y ♪

18:02.381 --> 18:03.940
Ever done
any musical theater?

18:04.016 --> 18:06.178
Well, I was in "Sound of Music"
when I was a kid.

18:06.251 --> 18:08.243
Oh, and I have
perfect spider pitch.

18:08.320 --> 18:10.687
I've found my Rusty.

18:10.756 --> 18:11.587
[telephone ringing ]

18:13.959 --> 18:15.985
Hello?
- Dr. Venture?

18:16.061 --> 18:17.552
Yes, this is
Thaddeus S. Venture.

18:17.629 --> 18:18.619
To whom am I speaking?

18:18.697 --> 18:21.132
Yeah, this is, uh,
Frank Bigtime

18:21.200 --> 18:23.567
from, uh,
Bigtime Productions.

18:23.635 --> 18:25.001
I just read
your "Rust!" script,

18:25.070 --> 18:27.630
and I got to tell you --
I think it's dynamite stuff.

18:27.706 --> 18:28.765
Can you come in for a meeting?

18:28.841 --> 18:30.901
Uh, sure! When?
- How about right now?

18:30.976 --> 18:33.377
Well, now works for me, too.
Where are you at?

18:33.445 --> 18:34.936
- Impossible Plaza.
- Impossible Plaza?

18:35.013 --> 18:35.912
[ chuckles ]

18:35.981 --> 18:37.916
I guess I'm not
the only superscientist

18:37.983 --> 18:38.814
who needs renters
to pay the mortgage, huh?

18:38.884 --> 18:40.182
- What?
- Oh, nothing.

18:40.252 --> 18:41.311
I'll be there.

18:41.386 --> 18:43.048
[ footsteps pounding ]

18:43.122 --> 18:43.953
Taxi!

18:44.022 --> 18:46.617
Impossible Plaza,
and step on it.

18:46.692 --> 18:48.593
You got it, buddy.

18:48.660 --> 18:50.652
[ keys clacking ]

18:52.000 --> 18:58.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

19:00.439 --> 19:01.771
[ chuckles ]

19:01.840 --> 19:03.809
[elevator bell dings ]

19:03.876 --> 19:07.210
Uh, hello?
Hello?

19:11.350 --> 19:12.181
What?

19:14.853 --> 19:15.843
[groans ]

19:15.921 --> 19:17.651
Hello? Hello?
Hello?

19:17.723 --> 19:20.454
Thank you for coming
on such short notice,

19:20.526 --> 19:21.994
Dr. Venture

19:22.060 --> 19:23.187
Phantom Limb?!

19:23.262 --> 19:25.060
Wait.
You're -- you're a producer now?

19:25.130 --> 19:27.531
Yes, and the reviews are in.

19:27.599 --> 19:31.627
I'm afraid Rusty will be ending
his run on Broadway tonight.

19:31.703 --> 19:34.901
Of course, I'll have to consult
with my partners first.

19:34.973 --> 19:37.408
Think you're getting out of here
alive, slim?

19:37.476 --> 19:38.307
Fat Chance!

19:38.377 --> 19:40.107
[gasping ]

19:40.179 --> 19:41.613
You shall not seek --

19:41.680 --> 19:45.208
and I will not accept --
your escape.

19:45.284 --> 19:48.550
- Aah!
- Going down?

19:48.620 --> 19:51.055
Boo!

19:51.123 --> 19:53.319
Take a bow,
Dr. Venture!

19:53.392 --> 19:56.885
This is your final
curtain call!

19:56.962 --> 19:57.793
[evil laughter]

20:01.066 --> 20:03.126
Aah!

20:03.202 --> 20:04.727
Way to go, new guy!

20:04.803 --> 20:05.634
What?

20:05.704 --> 20:07.536
I couldn't see
your invisible leg!

20:07.606 --> 20:10.440
Why the hell's it got to be so
dark in here, anyway, huh?

20:11.743 --> 20:13.336
Uh...

20:13.412 --> 20:15.347
ah!

20:15.414 --> 20:17.508
[gasps ]

20:17.583 --> 20:19.347
Where di--

20:19.418 --> 20:21.046
What -- where in blazes
did he go?!

20:21.119 --> 20:22.348
Aw, geez.

20:22.421 --> 20:24.515
Aw, he must have got sucked
into my enigma hole.

20:24.590 --> 20:26.024
Cody?

20:26.091 --> 20:27.081
Aah!

20:27.159 --> 20:30.755
Uh, remain calm, sir!
I will save you!

20:30.829 --> 20:32.092
[ keypad beeps ]

20:32.164 --> 20:35.032
Aah! Aah! Aah!

20:35.100 --> 20:36.762
Don't -- stop, drop,
and roll!

20:36.835 --> 20:38.201
Stop, drop, and roll!

20:38.270 --> 20:39.329
[ keypad beeps ]
Sir!

20:39.404 --> 20:41.032
- Aah! Aah!
- Wait!

20:41.106 --> 20:42.938
Aah!

20:44.009 --> 20:45.637
Wait!

20:45.711 --> 20:47.202
Wait, man on fire!

20:47.279 --> 20:49.839
Hey, I told you -- I don't know
where it goes, okay?

20:49.915 --> 20:51.281
It's completely random.

20:51.350 --> 20:53.910
This one time,
during a bank heist,

20:53.986 --> 20:55.579
I pulled a slip 'n slide,
The Beach Boys' "Pet Sounds,"

20:55.654 --> 20:58.123
and half a freakin' Roman legion
out of there.

20:58.190 --> 21:02.286
Aah!

21:02.361 --> 21:04.159
Fire,
Professor Impossible!

21:04.229 --> 21:06.289
It's fire!

21:06.365 --> 21:08.630
Please exit the building
via the fire stairs

21:08.700 --> 21:10.601
in a calm,
orderly manner.

21:10.669 --> 21:11.637
[ panting ]

21:11.703 --> 21:14.571
Quickly, gentlemen --
to the Impossi-car!

21:14.640 --> 21:18.008
But I thought we were calling it
The Revenge Mobile now.

21:18.977 --> 21:20.070
♪ I'm Rusty ♪

21:23.081 --> 21:25.073
♪ I'm Rusty ♪

21:31.923 --> 21:34.791
♪ the man of action ♪

21:34.860 --> 21:37.295
♪ like muscle mothers ♪

21:37.362 --> 21:39.354
♪ not brothers ♪

21:39.431 --> 21:42.299
♪ on grand adventures ♪

21:42.367 --> 21:44.734
♪ they push me with them ♪

21:44.803 --> 21:46.533
♪ for mayhem ♪

21:46.605 --> 21:47.436
♪ he's Rusty ♪

21:47.506 --> 21:49.407
- Hey.
- Hey.

21:49.474 --> 21:50.965
How was
<i>your</i> summer?

21:51.043 --> 21:54.070
Well, I think I may have watched
my career in superscience

21:54.146 --> 21:55.409
go up in smoke.

21:55.480 --> 21:58.416
But I may have managed to pull
my dreams from the ashes.

21:58.483 --> 21:59.451
How was yours?

21:59.518 --> 22:03.182
Oh, from what I hear,
it was amazing.

22:03.255 --> 22:04.553
H-Have you seen Pop?

22:04.623 --> 22:06.558
He left New York without even
saying goodbye.

22:10.929 --> 22:11.919
Daddy?

22:11.997 --> 22:13.295
Puh!
You should be so lucky.

22:13.365 --> 22:14.333
Ow!

22:14.399 --> 22:15.992
All right,
let's just take it easy.

22:16.068 --> 22:17.195
You just zip it, mister!

22:17.269 --> 22:19.135
And keep to your own dimension
from now on.

22:19.204 --> 22:21.105
Fine. I don't even like
your dimension, anyway.

22:21.173 --> 22:22.607
It's an asshole dimension.

22:22.674 --> 22:23.835
How do you like that?

22:23.909 --> 22:26.037
Oh, nice potty mouth
in front of the boys.

22:26.111 --> 22:28.706
Look, you're the Dean
of this dimension, right?

22:28.780 --> 22:31.045
Explain to the untalented
Mr. Ripley here

22:31.116 --> 22:33.278
he can't just waltz
into my dimension

22:33.352 --> 22:35.787
and try to kill me with a rock
and replace me

22:35.854 --> 22:38.949
just because I happen to have
more hair, more money,

22:39.024 --> 22:41.619
and a hit play on Broadway!

22:41.693 --> 22:42.786
♪ I'm Rusty ♪

